Study Regulations:
116. The review committee assesses the doctoral student's academic progress in research in credit points, considering the following criteria and the requirements defined by the faculty council [effective as of 01.09.2014]:
116.1. stage of the doctoral thesis;
116.2. printed publications related to the topic of the doctoral thesis that meet the requirements of clause 18 of the Procedure for Awarding Doctorates; [effective as of 01.01.2014]
116.3. participation in conferences and seminars related to the doctoral thesis, taking into account the level of these events and the doctoral student's contribution;
116.4. other research activities related to the doctoral thesis (practical training outside the university, participation in research projects, obtaining new methods, work at the library, etc.).
